
This directory is intended for PlatformIO Test Runner and project tests.

Unit Testing is a software testing method by which individual units of
source code, sets of one or more MCU program modules together with associated
control data, usage procedures, and operating procedures, are tested to
determine whether they are fit for use. Unit testing finds problems early
in the development cycle.

More information about PlatformIO Unit Testing:
- https://docs.platformio.org/en/latest/advanced/unit-testing/index.html

## Native test suites

In addition to the PlatformIO test runner, this directory contains standalone
native test suites: each is a `.cpp` file compiled directly with `c++`
(no PlatformIO/`pio` involved) via a `run_*_test.sh` script, and run as a
plain host binary.

| Suite | Test file | Run script |
|---|---|---|
| Differential rounding | `differential_rounding/DifferentialRoundingTest.cpp` | `run_differential_rounding_test.sh` |
| Release JSON parser | `release_json_parser/ReleaseJsonParserTest.cpp` | `run_release_json_parser_test.sh` |
| Streaming JSON parser | `streaming_json_parser/StreamingJsonParserTest.cpp` | `run_streaming_json_parser_test.sh` |
| `lib/DataStore` TimeSeriesStore | `timeseries_store/TimeSeriesStoreTest.cpp` | `run_timeseries_store_test.sh` |
| `lib/DataStore` RecordStore | `recordstore/RecordStoreTest.cpp` | `run_recordstore_test.sh` |
| `lib/DataStore` BookStore | `bookstore/BookStoreTest.cpp` | `run_bookstore_test.sh` |
| `lib/DataStore` ReadingLog | `readinglog/ReadingLogTest.cpp` | `run_readinglog_test.sh` |
| `lib/DataStore` BookCatalog | `bookcatalog/BookCatalogTest.cpp` | `run_bookcatalog_test.sh` |

Run any suite with:

```bash
./test/run_<suite>_test.sh
```

### DataStore suites

The `timeseries_store`, `recordstore`, `bookstore`, `readinglog`, and
`bookcatalog` suites cover `lib/DataStore/` (on-device physical-book catalog
and reading-session storage, see `docs/book-catalog-format.md`). They:

- Link the relevant `lib/DataStore/**` sources plus `lib/Logging/Logging.cpp`
  against the POSIX-file-backed `HalStorage`/`ESP` stubs vendored by the
  `env:simulator` PlatformIO environment at
  `.pio/libdeps/simulator/simulator/src/`, and ArduinoJson at
  `.pio/libdeps/simulator/ArduinoJson/src/`.
- Require the `simulator` PlatformIO environment to have been fetched at
  least once (so `.pio/libdeps/simulator/` exists), e.g. via `pio run -e simulator`.
- Use the shared harness in `datastore_common/TestHarness.h`, which provides
  `ASSERT_EQ`/`ASSERT_TRUE`/`ASSERT_FALSE`/`PASS()` macros and a
  `TempStorageDir` RAII helper that points `Storage` at a fresh temporary
  directory (via the `CROSSPOINT_SIM_SD`/`CROSSPOINT_EMU_SD` env vars used by
  the vendored simulator) for each test, removing it afterwards.
- Print `[SIM] open failed: ... No such file or directory` lines to stderr
  for expected "file/dir doesn't exist yet" probes (e.g. `Storage.exists()`
  checks before a directory is created) — this is normal simulator logging,
  not a test failure. Each suite prints `=== Results: N passed, M failed ===`
  at the end; a non-zero exit code indicates failure.
